author: Kat Bein
title: Unlike Pluto Plays Rock Star on 'Worst In Me': Exclusive
text:
Brett Smith Unlike Pluto 
Even electronic music producers want to play the rock star now and then, but not every dance DJ can play the part. Unlike Pluto has the presence and the skills to take center stage on “Worst In Me,” a guitar and synth heavy song the producer wrote, recorded, and sang all over. 
“Worst in Me” is dynamic and darkly alluring. It's almost industrial in its hook with stomping, echoing drums. It's dramatic and catchy in the best way, definitely has a lot of crossover potential. Check it out below, exclusively on Billboard Dance .
